The paper deals with a data recovery problem in compressed sensing using a partial Fourier matrix, which is a common approach in signal processing. The use of reweighted l1 minimization is also a common technique in CS. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the sparsity of the signal, which is a key concept in CS, making cs.MM (Mathematical Methods) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. Finally, the paper provides a theoretical analysis of the recovery algorithm, which involves probabilistic arguments, suggesting that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) could also be a relevant category.
